dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset containing 10 independent signals of size 128x128 generated using K = 3 atoms of size 5x5 and activation tensors of rank R* = 2, with added multivariate Gaussian noise.
dcterms:title: Synthetic Dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset of 32-channel EEG signals recorded at 250 Hz during General Anesthesia, focusing on the Recovery of Consciousness phase, with a tensor representation obtained through Short-Time Fourier Transform.
dcterms:title: EEG Dataset
